  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>As a Bonus Action, you can manifest a spectral tail as a natural weapon and immediately attack with it. If you hit with the tail, you deal Force damage equal to 1d6 plus your Strength modifier or Dexterity modifier (You choose this when you manifest the tail), instead of the Bludgeoning damage normal for an Unarmed Strike. Furthermore, if there are creatures within 5 feet of your initial target for your tail attack, you can deal Force damage equal to the modifier you chose when attacking them.</p><p>You can use this Bonus Action a number of times equal to your Proficiency Bonus, and you regain all expended uses when you finish a Long Rest. You can regain a use of this Bonus Action by expending a Hit Die (no action required).</p>",
